article.headline: High Point 78, Presbyterian 68
article.story: HIGH POINT, N.C. -- Allan Chaney finished with career-highs of 21 points and 12 rebounds to lift High Point past Presbyterian 78-68 Saturday night in Big South Conference play. John Brown added 20 points and Adam Weary chipped in 14 to help High Point (11-10, 6-3) win its fifth straight at home. The Panthers never trailed at any point in the game. Ahead 63-60 with 5:30 left to play, High Point extended its lead with a 7-2 run, going ahead 70-62 on Weary's layup with 2:29 remaining. The Panthers went 6 for 6 at the charity stripe in the final 1:01 to seal the victory. High Point shot 60 percent (15 of 25) and made 19 free throws in the second half, compared to 10 for Presbyterian. Joshua Clyburn finished with 17 points for the Blue Hose (5-18, 2-7), who have lost three of their last four games.
